    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-stir-fry-with-brown-rice-and-honey-chilli-cashews/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs on the diagonal</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-stir-fry-with-brown-rice-and-honey-chilli-cashews/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> and <strong>soy</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> in a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>honey</strong> (save the rest for later!), your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame</strong> <strong>oil</strong>, <strong>rice</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong> and 75ml [100ml] [125ml] <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>stir fry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-stir-fry-with-brown-rice-and-honey-chilli-cashews/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>cashew nuts</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-stir-fry-with-brown-rice-and-honey-chilli-cashews/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly toasted, add the<strong> remaining</strong> <strong>honey</strong> to the pan with your <strong>chilli</strong> <strong>flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 2-3 min or until caramelised</p><p>Once caramelised, transfer the cashew nuts to a plate to cool into a brittle and reserve the pan \u2013 these are your <strong>honey chilli cashews</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-stir-fry-with-brown-rice-and-honey-chilli-cashews/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>sweet pea pods </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-stir-fry-with-brown-rice-and-honey-chilli-cashews/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ginger</strong> <strong>paste</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>stir</strong> <strong>fry</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> and cook for a further 4 min or until the sauce has thickened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>cooled</strong> <strong>honey chilli cashews</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-pork-stir-fry-with-brown-rice-and-honey-chilli-cashews/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mince stir fry</strong> next to the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped honey chilli cashews</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the honey chilli cashews!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
